.Dd $Mdocdate: July 21 2026 $
.Dt FSCK_ZLFS 8
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm fsck_zlfs
.Nd check the consistency of a ZLFS file system
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Fl v
.Op Fl S Ar secsize
.Ar special | image
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
performs an offline, read-only consistency check of the ZLFS file
system on
.Ar special ,
or on a plain image file
.Ar image
(for example a
.Xr dd 1
dump of the device).
No zone commands are issued, so an image needs no zoned hardware.
.Pp
ZLFS is log-structured: nothing is ever repaired in place, because the
zone contract forbids overwrites and every commit is already atomic --
recovery from a bad newest generation is mounting an older one.
.Nm
therefore only reports.
.Pp
The check covers the superblock generation log (checksums, static
geometry agreement, newest-generation selection), the checkpoint and
inode map, every inode (identity, mode, link count, size bounds, a
full walk of the direct, single-, double- and triple-indirect trees
with range checks and cross-inode duplicate-block detection, and the
re-derived block count), the directory tree from the root
.Pq Dq \&. and Dq \&.. identity, dangling entries, cycles, link counts ,
and orphaned inodes.
.Pp
The options are as follows:
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl S Ar secsize
The device sector (LBA) size in bytes.
Defaults to 512.
.It Fl v
Verbose: print a line for every inode, including the LBA of its inode
block (useful for targeted corruption in tests).
.El
.Sh EXIT STATUS
.Nm
exits 0 when the file system is clean, 8 when inconsistencies were
found, and 1 on operational errors.
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr fsck 8 ,
.Xr mount_zlfs 8 ,
.Xr newfs_zlfs 8
